Of course, this is a very famous (Oddly enough, the same problem was in the IMO 1975) *Inequality*. Let $x+y=a$ and $xy=b$, then we have:
\begin{align*}
\left(x+\frac{1}{y}\right)\left(x+\frac{1}{y}-2018\right)+\left(y+\frac{1}{x}\right)\left(y+\frac{1}{x}-2018\right)&=a^2-2018a+2-\frac{a}{b}-4036 \frac{a}{b^2}+2038\left(2\sqrt{\frac{a}{b}} - \frac{1}{b}\right)\\
&= a^2+\frac{a}{b}+(2a-b)(2038-b)\left(\sqrt{\frac{a}{b}}-\frac{1}{b}\right).
\end{align*}
Now let $\sqrt{\frac{a}{b}}=t$, then we get
\begin{align*}
& (t^2-1)^2+\frac{2t^2-1}{t^2-1}+(2t^2-1)(2038t^2-2039)\\
= & (2037)t^4+(2t^4-3404t^2+3958305t^2-t^2+1),
\end{align*}
which is a convex *Polynomial*. Clearly the Minimum of the above $P(t)$ is at $t=\sqrt{1734}$. However, $t \ge 1$. Hence the value of the $P(t)$ is minimum at $t=1$, i.e. when $x=y=1$, and hence the Minimum of the above $P(t)$ is $3958306$ $\square$

<answer>$(x+y)^2-2018(x+y)+2-\left(\frac{x+y}{xy}\right)-4036\left(\frac{x+y}{(xy)^2}\right)+2038\left[2\sqrt{\frac{x+y}{xy}}-\frac{1}{xy}\right]$</answer>

